arXiv:2403.15232v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: We consider the Laplacian with drift in $\mathbb R^n$ defined by $\Delta_
u = \sum_{i=1}^n( rac{\partial^2}{\partial x_i^2} + 2 
u_i rac{\partial }{\partial{x_i}})$ where $
u=(
u_1,\ldots,
u_n)\in \mathbb R^n\setminus\{0\}$. The operator $\Delta_
u$ is selfadjoint with respect to the measure $d\mu_
u(x)=e^{2\langle
u,xangle}dx$. This measure is not doubling but it is locally doubling in $\mathbb R^n$. We define, for every $M>0$ and $k \in \mathbb N$, the operators $$ W^k_{
u,M,*}(f) = \sup_{t>0}\left|A^k_{
u,M,t}(f)ight|,\hspace{5mm}g_{
u,M}^k(f) = \left(\int_0^\infty\left|A^k_{
u,M,t}(f)ight|^2 rac{dt}{t}ight)^{ rac{1}{2}},\,k\geq 1, $$ the $ho$-variation operator $$ V_ho\left( \{A^k_{
u,M,t}\}_{t>0}ight)(f)= \sup_{0<t_1<\cdots<t_\ell,\,\ell \in \mathbb N}\left(\sum^{\ell-1}_{j=1}\left|A^k_{
u,M,t_j}(f)- A^k_{
u,M,t_{j+1}}(f)ight|^hoight)^{ rac{1}{ho}},\;\; ho>2, $$ and, if $\{t_j\}_{j\in \mathbb N}$ is a decreasing sequence in $(0,\infty)$, the oscillation operator $$ O(\{A_{
u,M,t}^k\}_{t>0},\{t_j\}_{j\in \mathbb N})(f)=\Big(\sum_{j\in \mathbb N}\;\;\sup_{t_{j+1}\leq \varepsilon <\varepsilon '\leq t_j}|A^k_{
u,M,\varepsilon}(f)-A^k_{
u,M,\varepsilon '}(f)|^2 \Big)^{1/2}. $$ where $A^k_{
u,M,t}=t^k\partial^k_t(I-t\Delta_
u)^{-M}$, $t>0$. We denote by $T_{
u,M}^k$ any of the above operators. We analyze the boundedness of $T^k_{
